news.title: Madras HC pat for Tamil Nadu fiat on registration of property
news.para: Though the action has been taken after several court orders addressing the issue, Madras high court has appreciated the timely action taken on part of the registration department in issuing the circular without complicating the issue by moving appeals against the order.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body earns Rs 1.5 crore on Day-1 of camp held to clear building proposals
news.para: As many as 29 proposals submitted by the developers and architects pending with the town planning department were cleared on the first day of the three-day camp.

news.title: Consult utility companies too before granting permit for multi-storied buildings: Kerala HC
news.para: A division bench comprising justices A Muhamed Mustaque and Shoba Annamma Eapen was considering an appeal filed by KWA challenging a single bench’s directive to provide water connection to an apartment complex in Kochi on a petition filed by a builder.

news.title: Kolkata: Hidco starts lottery for New Town co-operative plots
news.para: The plots, four to six cottahs each, will be for state employees, including cops. Type-1 of the housing will be for state employees, Type-2 will be for others.

news.title: Rajasthan housing board to focus on small towns for projects
news.para: Many of the 4,500 residential units that urban development and housing (UDH) minister Shantilal Dhariwal launched for this year on Wednesday are scheduled to come up in smaller towns.

news.title: Flat owners' associations in Karnataka now to be registered as cooperative society or company
news.para: By forming a cooperative society of apartment owners, the society becomes a corporate body which can convey the title of common areas as per section 17 of RERA 2016 and also gets legal incorporation status to sign the contracts with service providers. There are many advantages of having a body corporate society representing the association of owners, he informed.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency plea against N Kumar Housing for over Rs 60 crore loan default
news.para: Details of the insolvency petition show that the company which is the principal borrower and the one that stood as corporate guarantor had the same director — N Kumar.

news.title: Lucknow: FIR against Gauri Khan, Tulsiani Group's directors
news.para: The FIR was lodged by one Kirit Jaswant Shah, a resident of Mumbai. Shah in the FIR alleged that Gauri Khan became the brand ambassador of Tulsiani Construction and Developers Group in 2015.

news.title: Bombay HC warns MLA of contempt for obstructing redevelopment project
news.para: The court was hearing a contempt of court petition filed by SD Corp which is carrying out a redevelopment project in Antop Hill. Of 850 slums categorised as eligible huts by SRA, 820 were given possession of alternative accommodation.

news.title: Bombay HC says no stamp duty on redeveloped housing society apartments
news.para: The court has set aside and revoked earlier circulars which contemplate that a Permanent Alternate Allotment Agreement (PAAA) executed between the developer and members of the society requires it to be stamped again even though the development agreement executed between the developer and the society is already stamped.

news.title: NCLAT sets aside HDFC plea to stay IL&FS' BKC headquarters sale
news.para: HDFC had sanctioned a loan of Rs 400 crore to IL&FS as a lease rental discounting transaction in 2018. The repayment of this facility was to be from the cash flows generated from the use of the property being let out by IL&FS.

news.title: Bai Kabibai & Hansraj Morarji Charity Trust sells 23 acres in Mumbai for nearly Rs 540 crore
news.para: As part of the total consideration, the buyers will make a direct payment of Rs 450 crore to the trust. In addition to this, they will also transfer 140 residential units to the trust.

news.title: Over 1,000 builders respond to MahaRERA show-cause notices
news.para: While some developers have informed the regulatory body that they have already completed their projects, others have said they will renew their projects within a month.

news.title: Noida schemes to coax builders to pay up, force start registries find few takers
news.para: Last December, the Noida Authority floated a reschedulement policy, which builders could avail of between January 1 and March 31. The policy allowed realtors to restructure the payment of their total dues by paying up 20% upfront and agreeing to tranche payment within a two-year window.

news.title: NoBroker raises $5 million in Series E round from Google
news.para: "Current funding will be used to expand and improve Nobrokerhood. Currently it operates in 15,000 societies in 11 cities. We want to reach to one lakh societies in the next two years," said Amit Agarwal, co-founder and CEO of Nobroker.
